
[1]virtuous

   VIR'TUOUS, a.

   1. Morally good; acting in conformity to the moral law; practicing the
   moral duties, and abstaining from vice; as a virtuous man.

   2. Being in conformity to the moral or divine law; as a virtuous
   action; a virtuous life.

   The mere performance of virtuous actions does not denominate an agent
   virtuous.

   3. Chaste; applied to women.

   4. Efficacious by inherent qualities; as virtuous herbs; virtuous
   drugs. [Not in use.]

   5. Having great or powerful properties; as virtuous steel; a virtuous
   staff; a virtuous ring. [Not in use.]

   6. Having medicinal qualities. [Not used.]
